This paper deals with the placement of network functions and middleboxes in computer networks, which is a topic closely related to network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also presents a combinatorial proof and approximation algorithms, which are typical topics in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and theoretical computer science (cs.AL). The paper also discusses capacity constraints and communication routes, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SI).
